The code statements that lead to the bug are:
```java
DocumentBuilderFactory factory = DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance();
DocumentBuilder dbuilder = factory.newDocumentBuilder();
```
Reason:
The lack of configurability in the `DocumentBuilderFactory` allows the parser to process external entities and DOCTYPE declarations by default, making it vulnerable to XML External Entity (XXE) attacks. This means that malicious XML input could exploit these features, leading to potential security vulnerabilities.

The code statements that fix the bug are:
```java
factory.setFeature("http://xml.org/sax/features/external-general-entities", false);
factory.setFeature("http://xml.org/sax/features/external-parameter-entities", false);
factory.setFeature("http://apache.org/xml/features/disallow-doctype-decl", true);
```
Reason:
These statements configure the `DocumentBuilderFactory` to disable the processing of external entities and DOCTYPE declarations, thereby mitigating the risk of XXE attacks. By explicitly setting these features, the parser becomes more secure and robust against malicious XML input.

